# Behavior-Driven Development Skill

## Purpose
Guide an AI agent through Behavior-Driven Development as defined by its founders: Dan North (Introducing BDD, 2006), Matt Wynne and Aslak Hellesoy (Cucumber/Gherkin), and Seb Rose (BDD Books). This skill includes foundational test quality properties and the BDD practice of specifying behavior through examples in natural language.

## Sections to Generate

### When to Use This Skill
Describe scenarios: defining acceptance criteria, writing feature files, specifying business rules with examples, bridging communication between technical and non-technical stakeholders, implementing outside-in development, creating living documentation.

